Yup, I'm a big ass gimp, I have no idea how many hp's they have. 15k hp's???<br>
<br>
Some people dont like to trouble themselves with such trival bullshit. I have to remember enough shit day in day out with computers and programming. Knowing everything in a _video game_ does not perk my interest. I spend my time and Brain capacity on other important things, not memorizing the HP's of a monster in Everquest.<br>
<br>
When I get home from work. I enjoy relaxing, killing shit on EQ. Not trying to calculate how many nukes will it take to kill mob X if he resists my spells 10% of the time with each spell being partial resisted around ~30%. No thanks. I play to have fun and kill shit.<br>
<br>
You are correct in the game getting easier. I think thats a good thing. Its really not that much easier, you can still get your ass handed to you very easy in EQ. Newbie levels, try playing a newbie char to lvl-20 WITHOUT twinking. Its still a challenge, just not as hard as it was in the old days. No more spending 10 hours searching for your lvl-5 corpse, which would make people delete the char and start a new one.<br>
<br>
One thing that I dont understand though, is everyone wants to shoot for lvl-60. I still dont have a lvl-60 char in the 3 years that I have been playing. Got bunches of lvl-50+ chars, but not one lvl-60. It doesnt bother me at all, I just play a class I'm going to have fun with.<br>
<br>
Another thing that I dont understand is the why do people only hunt outdoor zones? Don't those zones get SOOOO boring, pulling single pull after single pull?<br>
<br>
I hate outdoor zones, I dread being a puller in an outdoor zone. All that running back and forth looking for a monster.<br>
<br>
